&amp; B. HOSTETTLER
</paragraph>
<caption id="B5E1AEAF7773FFB818F348BDFEF1EC84" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6448491" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6448491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6448491/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" startId="11.[151,186,938,960]" targetBox="[153,1428,259,894]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph id="E121FE277773FFB818F348BDFEF1EC84" blockId="11.[151,1441,937,988]" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 7: Transversalschliffe von 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB819AE48BDFD4BECE7" box="[458,673,938,959]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">
Ivanoviella 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47773FFB81A5848BDFD4BECE7" baseAuthorityName="Rollier" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[572,673,938,959]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="oxoniensis">oxoniensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. Exemplar von 21.5 mm Länge, 21.5 mm Breite und 21.5 mm Dicke. Massstab: 1 cm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E121FE277773FFB818F34F3EFD2BE9F6" blockId="11.[151,756,1065,1710]" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB818F34F3EFEAAEB19" bold="true" box="[151,320,1065,1089]" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Bemerkungen:</emphasis>
Rollier (1917) stützte sein neues Taxon auf 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47773FFB818A54F5EFD1AEB39" authority="Davidson, 1878" authorityName="Davidson" authorityYear="1878" box="[193,752,1097,1121]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="variety" species="varians" variety="spathica">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB818A54F5EFE41EB39" box="[193,427,1097,1121]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Rhynchonella varians</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB819864F5EFDD6EB39" box="[482,572,1097,1121]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">spathica</emphasis>
Davidson, 1878
</taxonomicName>
, und Laurin (1984) legte daraus (Taf. 28, 
<figureCitation id="79A5E2A27773FFB81A2D4F7DFD6DEBDA" box="[585,647,1130,1154]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[151,186,2054,2076]" captionTargetBox="[488,525,1749,1963]" captionTargetId="graphics-749@7.[488,520,1749,1865]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 5: Lithostratigraphisches Profil, Graitery-Member, La Vieille Copérie (Combe d’Eschert). (Koordinaten 597 250/233 650)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6448487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6448487/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) den Lectotyp fest. Makridin (1955), der die Gattung 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB81A184F9CFD1EEBFB" box="[636,756,1163,1187]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Ivanoviella</emphasis>
für Formen des Callovien (Jason-Zone) der russischen Plattform (Region Moskau, Kaspisches Meer) benutzte, bezog sie irrtümlich auf 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47773FFB819A54FFAFDBEEA5D" box="[449,596,1261,1285]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB819A54FFAFDBEEA5D" box="[449,596,1261,1285]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Rhynchonella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB81A084FF9FEE3EA7E" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">
= 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47773FFB81AEA4FFAFEE3EA7E" authorityName="Muir-Wood" authorityYear="1936" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonelloidella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">Rhynchonelloidella</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47773FFB8197A4E19FDC1EA7E" authority="Rollier, 1917" authorityName="Rollier" authorityYear="1917" box="[286,555,1294,1318]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="alemanica">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB8197A4E19FE67EA7E" box="[286,397,1294,1318]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">alemanica</emphasis>
Rollier, 1917
</taxonomicName>
(siehe dazu auch Makridin, 1964: S. 140-142, Taf.5, 
<figureCitation id="79A5E2A27773FFB81A7A4E39FD9DEA1E" box="[542,631,1326,1350]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStart-3="Fig" captionStartId-0="5.[151,186,2053,2075]" captionStartId-1="6.[151,186,2025,2047]" captionStartId-2="7.[151,186,2054,2076]" captionStartId-3="9.[151,186,1275,1297]" captionTargetBox-0="[695,736,1646,1964]" captionTargetBox-1="[245,323,1676,1847]" captionTargetBox-2="[488,525,1749,1963]" captionTargetBox-3="[159,1432,267,1197]" captionTargetId-0="graphics-695@5.[704,736,1796,1912]" captionTargetId-1="graphics-1266@6.[245,323,1676,1847]" captionTargetId-2="graphics-749@7.[488,520,1749,1865]" captionTargetId-3="figure-205@9.[151,1438,257,1198]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="6" captionTargetPageId-2="7" captionTargetPageId-3="9" captionText-0="Fig. 3: Ausschnitt aus dem lithostratographischen Profil, Bollement-Member südlich Côte de la Rise (Koordinaten 582 750/240 275)." captionText-1="Fig. 4: Lithostratigraphisches Profil durch das Herznach-Member im Steinbruch LiesbergAmtil, abgeändert nach Gründel &amp; Hostettler (2012). (Koordinaten 598 625/250 100)." captionText-2="Fig. 5: Lithostratigraphisches Profil, Graitery-Member, La Vieille Copérie (Combe d’Eschert). (Koordinaten 597 250/233 650)." captionText-3="Fig. 6: Rhynchonelliden. a: Fortunella? acutiloba (Eud.-Desl.), Liesberg Amtil, spätes Callovien, Athleta-Zone (FPJ 5038); b: Laevigaterhynchia triplicosa (Wisniew.-Zelichow.), Col de la Croix, spätes Callovien, Athleta-Zone (FPJ 5039); c: Laevigaterhynchia cf. triplicosa (Wisniew.-Zelichow.), Col de la Croix, frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone? (FPJ 5040); d: Ivanoviella oxoniensis (Rollier), frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone? (FPJ 5041); e: Kallirhynchia? sp.1, Tunnel du Graitery, frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone (FPJ 5042); f: Kallirhynchia? sp.2, Tunnel du Graitery, frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone (FPJ 5043); g: Septaliphoria orbignyana (Oppel), Craitery (Combe d’Eschert), mittleres Callovien, Coronatum-Zone (FPJ 5044); h: Robustirhynchia ehningensis (Quenst.), Liesberg Amtil, frühes Callovien, Calloviense-Zone (FPJ 5045). Massstäbe: 1 cm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6448483" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6448485" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6448487" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6448489" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6448483/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6448485/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6448487/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6448489/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Fig. 3-6</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47773FFB81AEA4E39FE66EA3F" authority="Muir-Wood" authorityName="Muir-Wood" authorityYear="1936" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonelloidella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB81AEA4E39FEE3EA3F" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Rhynchonelloidella</emphasis>
Muir-Wood
</taxonomicName>
ist 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB819D44E58FDC2EA3F" box="[432,552,1359,1383]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Ivanoviella</emphasis>
sehr ähnlich, wenn nicht identisch (vgl. Shi &amp; Grant, 1993). 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB81A184E67FD1EEAD0" box="[636,756,1392,1416]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Ivanoviella</emphasis>
bleibt als eigenständige Gattung umstritten, obwohl Alméras 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB8189F4EA5FEDFEA91" box="[251,309,1457,1481]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
(1991) ihr mit 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB819804EA6FD57EA91" box="[484,701,1457,1481]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Ivanoviella gaetanii</emphasis>
eine neue Typusart zugrunde legten. Sie wurde von Laurin (1984) eingehend revidiert und durch die Subspezies 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47773FFB818F34D03FEE2E973" baseAuthorityName="Rollier" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[151,264,1556,1579]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="oxoniensis">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB818F34D03FEE2E973" box="[151,264,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">oxoniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB819234D04FE45E973" box="[327,431,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">rullyensis</emphasis>
präzisisiert. Ein Beispiel für die Schwierigkeit, mit diesen sich sehr ähnlichen Formen umzugehen, lieferte Wisniewska-Zelichowska (1978), indem sie 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB819604D62FE96E9D5" box="[260,380,1653,1677]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Ivanoviella</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47773FFB819E64D62FD76E9D5" authority="sensu Makridin" authorityName="sensu Makridin" authorityYear="1955" box="[386,668,1653,1677]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="alemanica">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB819E64D62FE1BE9D5" box="[386,497,1653,1677]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">alemanica</emphasis>
sensu Makridin
</taxonomicName>
für eine Form aus dem späten Bajocien (!) von 
<collectingCountry id="9989BEB77773FFB81A534D81FD9EE9F6" box="[567,628,1686,1710]" name="Poland" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Polen</collectingCountry>
angab.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E121FE277773FFB818F34DC0FDD5E80A" blockId="11.[151,756,1751,1874]" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB818F34DC0FDEBE9A8" bold="true" box="[151,513,1751,1776]" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Bisher bekannte Vorkommen:</emphasis>
Mittleres bis spätes Callovien von 
<collectingCountry id="9989BEB77773FFB8195A4DEFFE58E848" box="[318,434,1784,1808]" name="France" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Frankreich</collectingCountry>
(Dép. Saône-et-Loire, südliches 
<collectingRegion id="235A30C57773FFB818AA4C0EFEC5E869" box="[206,303,1817,1841]" country="France" name="Bourgogne" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Burgund</collectingRegion>
), Athleta-Zone von Oxford 
<collectingCountry id="9989BEB77773FFB81A3D4C0DFD68E869" box="[601,642,1818,1841]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">UK</collectingCountry>
, unsichere Angaben (Lieb, 1945) aus der 
<collectingCountry id="9989BEB77773FFB819B94C2DFDD1E80A" box="[477,571,1850,1874]" name="Switzerland" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Schweiz</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E121FE277773FFB818D04C6CFD55E74E" blockId="11.[151,727,1915,2070]" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">
Oberfamilie Hemithiridoidea Rzhonsnitskaia, 1956 Familie 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47773FFB819214C8BFEB0E88D" authority="Makridin, 1955 Unterfamilie" authorityName="Makridin" authorityYear="1955" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Cyclothyrididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="family">Cyclothyrididae Makridin, 1955 Unterfamilie</taxonomicName>
Cyclothyridinae Makridin, 1955 Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47773FFB819324CCAFEE8E74E" authority="Leidhold, 1921 Typusart" authorityName="Leidhold" authorityYear="1921" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Cyclothyrididae" genus="Septaliphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB819324CCAFE0DE8AD" box="[342,487,2013,2037]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Septaliphoria</emphasis>
Leidhold, 1921 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB818F34CE9FEE8E74E" bold="true" box="[151,258,2046,2070]" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Typusart</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB819674CE9FEE2E74E" bold="true" box="[259,264,2046,2070]" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47773FFB8196A4CE9FD55E74E" authority="Oppel, 1857" authorityName="Oppel" authorityYear="1857" box="[270,703,2046,2070]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="arduennensis">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357773FFB8196A4CE9FDDEE74E" box="[270,564,2046,2070]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Rhynchonella arduennensis</emphasis>
Oppel, 1857
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
